message.content:
1. A per-protocol analysis was conducted.
2. The analysis measured the parasitological and clinical failure rate at day 28 post treatment (PCF28).
3. The PCF28 was lower in the AS+AQ group compared to the AL or AS+CD groups.
4. The corrected PCF28 for re-infections in the AS+AQ group was 6.6%.
5. The corrected PCF28 for re-infections in the AL group was 13.8%.
6. The corrected PCF28 for re-infections in the AS+CD group was also 13.8%.
7. The p-value for the corrected PCF28 comparison was 0.08.
8. The uncorrected PCF28 in the AS+AQ group was 14.6%.
9. The uncorrected PCF28 in the AL group was 27.6%.
10. The uncorrected PCF28 in the AS+CD group was 28.1%.
11. The p-value for the uncorrected PCF28 comparison was 0.005.

messages.content:
Statement: In a per-protocol analysis, the parasitological and clinical failure rate at day 28 post treatment (PCF28) was lower in the AS+AQ group compared to the AL or AS+CD groups (corrected for re-infections: 6.6% vs 13.8% and 13.8% respectively, p = 0.08; uncorrected: 14.6% vs 27.6% and 28.1% respectively, p = 0.005).
